HEADWORD: Saddlery
<hw>Sad"dler*y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The
materials for making saddles and harnesses; the articles usually offered
for sale in a saddler's shop.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The trade or employment of a saddler.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Saddle-shaped</ent>⟦br⟧
